verses.roman:
eta bali' prabhu tāṅre kailā āliṅgana
rūpa gosāñi śire dhare prabhura caraṇa

synonyms: eta bali'-saying this; prabhu—Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; tāṅre—unto Rūpa Gosvāmī; kailā āliṅgana—embraced; rūpa gosāñi—Śrīla Rūpa Gosvāmī; śire—on the head; dhare—takes; prabhura caraṇa—the lotus feet of Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu.
translation: Having thus spoken, Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu embraced Rūpa Gosvāmī, who then placed the lotus feet of the Lord upon his head.
